race.comment: BELTA OF A SONG (2) looks to have been disappointing last campaign, though on closer inspection, she raced in much stronger company throughout. Back to CL3 today looks ideal and she's trialled coming into this with Pike on board, who sticks with her first-up. Can resume on a positive note. SHAMILIAN MISS (4) trialled well coming into this campaign and ran a strong race first-up, beaten 0.6L. She'll be better for that effort and Parnham now hops in the saddle. The barrier should see her in a good position in the run and she can go one better now. IMPRESSIVE JEWEL (5) comes here without a trial, though she has been placed in both fresh attempts. Back in trip today on the fresh side, but Faithfull knows her well and she can run a cheeky race. SWEET SURRENDER (8) will be fitter for a recent trial coming in and has plenty of upside being a lightly raced mare. Can put her best foot forward. MYSTIC JANE (1) can improve with the fresh run under her belt.
